The FBI has opened an inquiry into the murders of Yusor Mohammad Abu-Salha, Deah Shaddy Barakat, and Razan Mohammad Abu-Salha in Chapel Hill, North Carolina. The White House is also looking into whether federal laws were violated. President Obama expressed his condolences to the victims' loved ones and emphasized that no one in the United States should be targeted based on their identity, appearance, or religious beliefs. He highlighted the unity and diversity of the American people, as shown by the large turnout at the victims' funeral. The President quoted one of the victims, Yusor, who said that growing up in America was a blessing because people from different backgrounds and religions can come together as one.